What is a Semiconductor Packaging Mold Cleaner?
Semiconductor packaging mold cleaners are specialized chemical formulations developed to remove epoxy residues, flux deposits, mold release agents, carbonized contaminants, and microscopic particles from semiconductor packaging molds after molding operations.
These cleaners play a vital role in maintaining mold cleanliness, extending tool life, improving packaging quality, and minimizing production defects. As semiconductor devices continue to become smaller, more complex, and densely integrated, maintaining contamination-free mold surfaces has become critical for ensuring package reliability and manufacturing efficiency.
Modern mold cleaning solutions are engineered to meet the strict cleanliness standards required for advanced semiconductor packaging technologies, including Fan-Out Wafer-Level Packaging (FOWLP), 2.5D/3D ICs, System-in-Package (SiP), chiplet architectures, and heterogeneous integration.
